LogFile.FinalText: In many homes, you find a pet and most people prefer either a dog or a cat. So far, the soft puppee is more popular than the dear little kitten in the contest to become the most popular pet in Denmark. While the dog's loyalty explains why it is so popular, most owners of cats love its independent style. While the typical cat owner thinks that a dog is too dependent and dirty, many owners of dogs find cats lazy and without a personality. Many pet owners choose a pet that reflects their own personality. When the big, strong man buys a big, strong dog, the characteristics of the dog intensify the ego of the dog owner. In contrast, feminine women often prefer the beautiful and elegant cat. If they are used to each other, the dog and the cat usually get along very well. Often the owners of dogs and cats fight more than the dog and the cat.
